<paragraph id="8B83B373A648221238EB395F0A982D7E" blockId="13.[189,1399,559,698]" box="[189,416,559,587]" pageId="13" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="B9486F61A648221238EB395F0A0E2D7C" bold="true" box="[189,310,559,585]" pageId="13" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83B373A648221138EB392C08942EBD" blockId="13.[189,1399,559,698]" lastBlockId="14.[189,1400,265,392]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="97" pageId="13" pageNumber="96">
Body length 
<quantity id="4CC41E96A64822123901392C0AD02D42" box="[343,488,604,631]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.55" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.3" pageId="13" pageNumber="96" unit="mm" value="3.55" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.8 mm</quantity>
; antenna longer than body, F15 2.0 × its width (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64822123C72392C0FBC2D42" box="[1060,1156,604,631]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-82@13.[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Microplitis kaszabi Papp, 1980, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0047. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690342" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690342/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="96">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
); anteromesoscutum rugulose, notauli well defined by rugosity, mesoscutellar disc coriaceous (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64822123C7E390E0FBC2DAD" box="[1064,1156,637,664]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-82@13.[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Microplitis kaszabi Papp, 1980, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0047. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690342" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690342/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="96">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma length 2.5 × its width; vein R1 shorter than pterostigma (i.e., vein R1 distinctly longer than pterostigma half); in 1 
<superScript id="7C491E3BA64B221138BA3A790BCF2E22" attach="left" box="[236,247,265,279]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">st</superScript>
discal cell length 1.2–1.3 × its width; vein 1CUb 1.7–1.8 × as long as vein 1CUa (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64B22113C893A790E072E11" box="[1247,1343,265,292]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-82@13.[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Microplitis kaszabi Papp, 1980, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0047. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690342" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690342/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
); T1 rugulose, more or less broadening posteriorly and T1 length 1.5–1.6 × its maximum width (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64B22113D5D3A5A0E522E70" box="[1291,1386,298,325]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-82@13.[198,1390,748,1922]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 6. Microplitis kaszabi Papp, 1980, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0047. A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690342" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690342/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="97">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Colour: body black; antenna brown; tegula, scape, T2, T3 and legs (except for black metacoxa) yellow; pterostigma dark brown to black with a small basal yellow spot.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
